            "en-x-generated": "<h3>For which enterprises?</h3><p>To be eligible for this grant, the company must <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/ecologisch-en-veilig-transport/wie-en-welke-uitgaven-komen-aanmerking\">meet certain conditions</a>. The main conditions are that the enterprise:</p><ul><li>must have <strong>at least 1 motor vehicle </strong>(truck or tractor) <strong>or composite vehicle</strong> (tractor + semi-trailer/trailer)<ul><li>that is registered in Belgium</li><li>and is intended or used for transporting<strong>goods by</strong> road</li><li>and whose maximum authorised total weight (MTT) exceeds <strong>3.5 tonnes</strong>.</li></ul></li><li>must have an operating seat in the Flemish Region (according to the Crossroads Bank for Enterprises (CBE))</li><li>must have an <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/ecologisch-en-veilig-transport/wie-en-welke-uitgaven-komen-aanmerking\">accepted legal form</a>.</li></ul><h3>Which expenses are eligible?</h3><p>The grant can only be used for well-defined expenses that appear on the official <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/media/1382\">list of eligible expenses</a>. These expenditures include:</p><ul><li>driving assistance systems that promote energy-efficient and road-safe driving behaviour, such as a lane change correction system, a lane change assistance system, an adaptive cruise control (ACC), an alcohol lock</li><li>additional safety features that go beyond what the law requires, e.g. driver assistance and camera systems such as axle load meters, camera systems for rear parking and driving, brake retarders...</li><li>additional features with a positive impact on the environment, such as aerodynamic measures that reduce air resistance, low-noise and low-noise tyres, tyres with optimal rolling resistance...</li><li>measures that promote efficiency, in particular transport management and transport planning systems</li><li>measures promoting ergonomic design of the driving position, in particular air conditioning systems</li><li>measures to prevent theft, such as alarm systems, immobilisation systems, security systems...</li></ul><p>Since the 2021 application, a new <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/media/1382\">list of supported measures and support rates</a> is in force. What is new is that a number of measures also have an explanation that must be met.</p><p><strong>Expenditure means</strong> the purchase, rental or leasing of eligible services and goods. The expenditure (contracts or invoices) must relate to trucks over 3.5 tonnes and <strong>date from after 1 January 2017</strong>. The measures may be on the truck, tractor or semi-trailer/trailer.</p><h3>Expenditure that is not eligible</h3><ul><li>expenditure or measures on vehicles remaining in <strong>the business for less than three years</strong></li><li>expenditure on measures required by law</li><li>expenditure on measures that modify the vehicle's homologation and for which no new approval has been obtained</li><li>expenditure that is part of the enterprise's ordinary operating expenditure, non-specialised advice</li><li>installation costs.</li></ul>"
