            "en-x-generated": "<p>In all European Union countries, energy-intensive companies pay through their electricity bills for so-called 'emission rights' through which energy producers buy the right to emit a certain amount of greenhouse gases. As energy producers pass on the cost of buying emission rights, customers pay more for their electricity and face a competitive disadvantage compared to companies in regions with less ambitious climate policies.</p><p>Sixteen industries are eligible for the measure. These include producers from the metal, paper and chemical sectors.</p><p>Specifically, the applicant company must carry out an activity belonging to 1 of 16 specific NACE codes, which you can find on the VLAIO website. There you can also read what other conditions the company must meet and exactly which expenses are eligible.</p>",
